message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The symptoms and findings suggest a diagnosis of Wilms tumor, which is caused by a loss of function mutation of the zinc finger transcription factor. Hypoxia-inducible factor 1a inhibition is seen in certain cancers, but not in Wilms tumor. Deficiency of 17α-hydroxylase is seen in congenital adrenal hyperplasia and increased expression of insulin-like growth factor 2 is seen in Beckwith-Wiedemann syndrome, both of which are unrelated to Wilms tumor.
